South Africa  may produce 4.3 percent
more wheat this season than previously forecast, according to
the countryâ€™s Crop Estimates Committee.  The country may produce 1.85 million metric tons on higher-
than-expected yields, Marda Scheepers, an official at the
agency, said by phone from  Pretoria  today.  The committee also forecast that the barley crop will
increase 5.9 percent to 300,910 tons. The canola harvest is
